THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 432.037 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 432.037 1. The Trust Fund for Child Welfare is hereby
3 created. All benefits for survivors or other awards payable to
4 children receiving child welfare services pursuant to NRS 432.010
5 to 432.085, inclusive, in a county whose population is less than
6 100,000 must be deposited in the State Treasury for credit to the
7 Fund.
8 2. The Division shall:
9 (a) Keep a separate account for each child who receives money.
10 (b) [Deduct from the account any services to the child provided
11 by public money. Any surplus remaining may be expended for
12 extraordinary items deemed beneficial to the child.
13 (c)] Remit any [surplus] balance to the parent or legal guardian
14 of the child, or to the child if the child is emancipated or has reached
15 the age of 18 years, when the Division is no longer legally
16 responsible for the child.
17 3. The Division shall pay interest to each child’s separate
18 account maintained in the Trust Fund for Child Welfare at the end
19 of each interest period. Interest must be paid at a rate equal to the
20 average of the interest rates quoted by at least three banking
21 institutions for interest-bearing savings accounts of $3,000 or less
22 on the first day of each interest period. Interest must be paid on the
23 child’s account commencing with the first interest period that the
24 Division is legally responsible for the child. Interest must not be
25 paid for the interest period during which the child ceases to be the
26 legal responsibility of the Division.
27 4. All benefits for survivors or other awards payable to
28 children receiving child welfare services in a county whose
29 population is 100,000 or more pursuant to NRS 432.010 to 432.085,
30 inclusive, must be deposited in the trust fund for child welfare
31 established in the county treasury. A disbursement from the benefits
32 for survivors or other awards of a child which is deposited in the
33 fund may be made to the agency which provides child welfare
34 services for any child welfare services provided to the child with
35 public money.
36 5. As used in this section, “interest period” means that period
37 not less frequent than quarterly, as determined by the State
38 Treasurer, for which interest must be paid.
39 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
